
create database showme;
-- drop database showme;
use showme;
create table simpleUsers(
personal_id int not null,
f_name nvarchar(30) not null,
l_name nvarchar(30) not null,
phone nvarchar(15) not null,
address nvarchar(200) not null,
user_password nvarchar(30) not null,
user_email varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL,
user_type nvarchar(20),
primary key(personal_id)
);

create table auditorium_Owners(
personal_id int not null,
f_name nvarchar(30) not null,
l_name nvarchar(30) not null,
phone nvarchar(15) not null,
address nvarchar(200) not null,
user_password nvarchar(30) not null,
user_email varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL,
user_type nvarchar(20),
primary key( personal_id)
);

create table artists(
personal_id int not null,
f_name nvarchar(30) not null,
l_name nvarchar(30) not null,
phone nvarchar(15) not null,
address nvarchar(200) not null,
user_password nvarchar(30) not null,
user_email varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL,
user_type nvarchar(20),
primary key(personal_id)
);

create table auditorium_type(
auditorium_type_id int auto_increment,
auditorium_type_description nvarchar(100),
primary key(auditorium_type_id)
);

create table auditoriums(
auditorium_id int auto_increment,
auditorium_name nvarchar(30),
auditorium_address nvarchar(200),
auditorium_owner int not null,
auditorium_capacity int not null,
auditorium_type int not null,
auditorium_price int not null,
primary key(auditorium_id),
foreign key(auditorium_owner) references auditorium_Owners(personal_id),
foreign key(auditorium_type) references auditorium_type(auditorium_type_id)
);

create table shows_types(
show_type_id int auto_increment,
show_type nvarchar(30),
primary key(show_type_id)
);
create table shows(
id int auto_increment,
id_of_presenter int,
show_name nvarchar(200) not null,
show_description nvarchar(250) not null,
type_of_show int not null,
show_price int not null,
show_date nvarchar(30) not null,
show_location int not null,
numberOfTickets int ,
show_url text(500000),
primary key(id),
foreign key(show_location) references auditoriums(auditorium_id),
foreign key(type_of_show) references shows_types(show_type_id)
);
